1.  List all of the annotations you learned from class and homework to annotaitons.md
    
    > Done In /ShortQuestions/hw42/annotations.md

2.  what is the @configuration and @bean?

    > `@configuration` is place to write some global bean, to set up the singleton functions and set up properties/ 

3.  How do you handle the exception in Spring?

    > Try Catch in the function and try to finish the exception in the function. 
    > throws exception away. 
    > Use Global Exception Handler

4.  How do you do the validations in Spring? And list some validation annotaitons you know.
   
    > In entity, you write the limitation like `@NotNull,@Min(),@Max(),` etc. And in controller, for parameter, you write `@Valid` to check the data.  

5.  What is the actuator

    > Tool to monitor the project data like property, thread ... etc. 